Vice President Pence visited Walter Reed Medical Center in Bethesda, Maryland to express gratitude to service members and their families for their sacrifices. He conveyed greetings from President Trump and thanked them for their service and courage. Pence emphasized that the American people are grateful for their dedication and sacrifice, especially during the holiday season. He acknowledged the physical challenges many have faced and assured them that they are in the hearts of all Americans celebrating Christmas. Pence expressed appreciation to the USO Operations Center for their support of soldiers and their families. The visit concluded with a message of merry Christmas from Pence and his family to the service members and their families.